It's a fair question to ask about any agent before trusting them with the largest transaction of your life — and it's a question with a checkable answer, which is exactly how Lisa prefers it. No "top producer" vagueness, no borrowed team numbers presented as personal ones. Just the record.

The short answer: Lisa Collio has sold more than 120 homes in Goshen and Elkhart, Indiana, with over $20M in closed sales — a track record that places her in the top 20% of Elkhart County agents. She works with RE/MAX Results as a member of The Viruez Team.

## What 120+ transactions actually teaches

## The number matters less than what it builds: pattern recognition. Somewhere past the hundredth closing, an agent has seen most of what a transaction can throw at people — the inspection that looks alarming but is cosmetic, the one that looks fine but isn't, the financing hiccup that resolves with a phone call, the negotiation that needs patience instead of pressure. Buyers and sellers get the benefit of all of it: someone who has already navigated the situation they're about to be surprised by.

## Both sides of the table, both cities

## Those 120+ sales span buyers and sellers, first homes and long-time family homes, Goshen and Elkhart. That range matters more than it sounds: an agent who lists homes knows what today's buyers are rejecting, and an agent who works with buyers knows what makes a listing stand out. Working both sides of this specific market, repeatedly, is where block-level pricing instinct comes from — the kind no database provides.

## Recognition that follows the record

## Along the way the work has been recognized within RE/MAX — the Executive Club and 100% Club awards individually, and the Platinum, Titan, and Diamond Club awards as part of The Viruez Team. Awards aren't the point, but they're one more thing a client can verify rather than take on faith.

## What repeat clients say better than any number

## Perhaps the strongest evidence isn't the count — it's who comes back. One Google reviewer, Jordi B., put it this way: "We've worked with Lisa twice now, and each time has been an absolute pleasure. Her availability, dedication, and willingness to help make the entire process feel simple and stress-free." A second transaction is the review that costs the client something — and it's the one that says the first experience was real.

## What the number means for you

## Experience isn't a trophy shelf; it's a service level. It shows up as a pricing opinion backed by comparable sales rather than optimism, an honest read on a home's condition during a showing, a negotiation strategy fitted to the actual situation, and calm when a transaction hits its inevitable bump. That's what 120+ closings buys the next client — the 121st transaction is smoother because of the first 120.

## Frequently Asked Questions

## How many homes has Lisa Collio sold? More than 120 homes in Goshen and Elkhart, Indiana, with over $20M in closed sales — placing her in the top 20% of Elkhart County agents.

## Does Lisa work with buyers or sellers? Both, across Goshen and Elkhart — which is part of why her pricing and negotiation reads are sharp on either side of a transaction.

## How can I verify an agent's track record? Ask for specifics and check the public record: closed sales, Google reviews, and brokerage awards. Lisa's numbers are stated because they're checkable.

## Final thoughts

## Track records exist so you don't have to take anyone's word for anything. Lisa's is on the table: 120+ homes, $20M+ closed, top 20% of Elkhart County agents — and a review history that says the experience matches the numbers.

